{meta: title The Echo of Your Footsteps}
{meta: artist Faron Young}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]The day that you told me  you [C7]wanted to be [F]free
I [G7]agreed with everything you had to [C]say
But [C]I'll confess I lied  and [C7]darling how I [F]cried
When the [G7]echo of your footsteps died [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
I [G7]thought our castle had a firm [C]foundation
But [D7]all along was only made of [G7]clay
[C]With aching heart I found it crumbled [C7]to the [F]ground
When the [G7]echo of your footsteps died [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
If I had only known  [C7]I'd feel so all [F]alone
I'd [G7]have begged down on my knees for you to [C]stay
The gate [C]to paradise was [C7]closed before my [F]eyes
When the [G7]echo of your footsteps died [C]away
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
No [G7]matter where you are  I wish you well [C]dear
And [D7]I'll ask God to bless you [G7]everyday
For I [C]cannot deny  I bid [C7]my heart [F]goodbye
When the [G7]echo of your footsteps died [C]away
{end_of_verse}
